column14: George Moscone's & Harvey Milk's legacy of fighting for equal rights & human dignity is more important than ever due to @POTUS' attacks on our #LGBTQ communities. On this 40th anniversary of their murders, let's honor that legacy by fighting for the America they envisioned!  https://t.co/kG5tC4Ay5C

It’s beyond disgusting for @POTUS to release a statement so trite and full of lies. Open source reports and our allies’ actions have told us what we need to know about Khashoggi’s murder. Only someone so compromised would bury his head this deep in the Saudi sand.

On an AM flight, a passenger told me to keep pursuing the #RussiaInvestigation but urged me and my colleagues to look deeper into the #Khashoggi murder — “This is about who we are. Are we a nation of transactions or values?”
“The police may have ‘evidence,’ but I talked to my client and he said he didn’t do it.” — Reasoning that has persuaded ZERO juries from ever clearing someone accused of murder. #Khashoggi

.@realDonaldTrump is one turkey who should not be pardoned this #Thanksgiving. This week Trump helped the Saudis cover up the truth in #Khashoggi’s murder, attacked the Bin Laden raid leader, savaged an ind. judiciary, & avoided (again) going to a war zone to thank our troops.

column14: And let us also keep the 420,000 federal employees who are working during the holidays without pay because of the #TrumpShutdown in our thoughts. We are grateful that they are fulfilling their responsibilities to our country even when the president is not.
